entry.title: At G-20 Summit, U.S. Agrees to Relax Tariffs on European Steel
entry.content: Biden and European leaders worked to defuse trade tensions at the gathering in Rome, where Western leaders also called on Iran to comply with a nuclear accord.

entry.title: Ai Weiwei Traces a Century of Making Authorities Squirm
entry.content: A new memoir by world-famous artist-provocateur Ai Weiwei, “1000 Years of Joys and Sorrows,” traces a century of his family’s ups and downs with authorities; it’s being published in more than 20 countries—though not China.

entry.title: Haiti's Powerful Gangs Hold Country Hostage Over Fuel
entry.content: The country’s largest gang has blocked access to the fuel terminal that provides 70% of gas supplies, demanding the prime minister’s resignation.
